SIMPLE: wistful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wistful
<hw>Wist"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>wishful</ets>; perhaps influenced by <ets>wistly</ets>, which is
probably corrupted from OE. <ets>wisly</ets> certainly (from Icel.
<ets>viss</ets> certain, akin to E. <ets>wit</ets>). See
<er>Wish</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Longing; wishful; desirous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lifting up one of my sashes, I cast many a <qex>wistful</qex>,
melancholy look towards the sea.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of thought; eagerly attentive; meditative;
musing; pensive; contemplative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That he who there at such an hour hath been,⟦br⟧
Will <qex>wistful</qex> linger on that hallowed spot.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wist"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wist"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wistit</ent>⟦br⟧
